Dear Hiring Team,

I am writing to apply for the *Software Engineer* role at *DHI Group, Inc.* I bring more than three years of experience building production backend systems, AI-native workflow automation, and user-facing applications with *TypeScript*, *React*, *AWS*, and cloud-native services, along with a Master of Science in Computer Science from Pace University.

At Sperse, I built a *multi-agent* CRM platform in *Python*, *LangGraph*, *LangChain*, and *FastAPI* for 10,000+ users, routing work across 40+ specialized sub-agents with tenant-aware access control and prompt-injection defenses. I also shipped a *React* and *TypeScript* workflow builder for creating, running, and managing agent swarms with durable, resumable execution, and built an *AI-native* code-review pipeline by integrating *Claude Code* with a custom *FastMCP* review server to automate daily PR triage across 25-30 PRs/week. That mix of product engineering, workflow design, and automation lines up closely with the end-to-end candidate and recruiter experience you are rebuilding at Dice.

My earlier work at Qualitest strengthened the operational side of that foundation. I designed a cloud-agnostic Storage Service in *Java* and *Spring Boot* with *PostgreSQL* and *Redis* that handled uploads, downloads, and deletions across *Google Cloud Storage*, *S3*, and *MinIO* via expiring signed URLs. I also reduced query latency by optimizing *PostgreSQL* with window functions, materialized views, and indexes, exposed the results through interactive *React* visualizations, and orchestrated long-running jobs with *AWS Step Functions* to reduce *AWS Lambda* timeouts and improve error recovery across *100K+* weekly executions. Those are the kinds of production systems, cloud-native workflows, and quality-focused practices I would bring to your team.

DHI Group's mission of *Connecting Futures Now* and its *One Team* culture, with a strong emphasis on collaboration, growth, and giving back, is the kind of environment where I do my best work. I value shipping incrementally, reviewing code carefully, and using AI as a core part of how I build, not as a side experiment. I would welcome the chance to contribute to this team's mission and help improve the candidate and recruiter experience.

I would appreciate the opportunity to discuss my fit for *this team and its mission*. I can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration.

